INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES (1,'What is an \"evil twin\" Wi-Fi network?','A network that doubles your connection speed','A personal hotspot from your phone','A fake Wi-Fi hotspot set up by an attacker to trick you into connecting','A private home Wi-Fi','C','Beginner','Public WiFi Risks'),(2,'Which of the following is a common sign that an email might be phishing?','The email arrives from a domain you always use','The email uses your real full name in the greeting','The email has spelling errors and weird grammar','The email contains only plain text with no links','C','Beginner','Phishing emails'),(3,'Why can using public Wi-Fi be risky?','Because it always has a strong password','Because strangers on the same network might intercept your data','Because your phone would not be charge','Because it boosts internet speed','B','Beginner','Public WiFi Risks'),(4,'What is an OTP scam?','A promo code for discounts','A trick where scammers get you to share your one-time password','A bank service update','A phone network upgrade','B','Beginner','OTP scams'),(5,'What should you check before entering personal info on a website?','If the website loads fast','If the URL starts with https and has a padlock icon','If the background color is pretty','If the site has lots of ads','B','Beginner','Safe Browsing'),(6,'Which statement about OTPs is TRUE?','OTPs can be safely shared with customer care executives','OTPs should be posted in group chats for verification','OTPs are private codes and should never be shared with anyone','OTPs remain valid for several days','C','Beginner','OTP scams'),(7,'A safe browsing habit is to:','Use the same weak password everywhere','Download files from unknown pop-ups','Only click links from trusted sources','Allow every site to access your camera','C','Beginner','Safe Browsing'),(8,'If an email claims you must \"act now to avoid losing access to your account,\" what red flag is this showing?','Legitimate company urgency','Sense of urgency designed to rush you','Proper business communication','A friendly reminder','B','Beginner','Phishing emails'),(9,'What is a warning sign that a website might be unsafe?','It asks you to solve a captcha','It automatically starts downloading strange files','It has normal spelling and design','It asks you to sign in','B','Beginner','Safe Browsing'),(10,'According to phishing guidance, what should you do if an unexpected email asks for passwords or credit card details?','Click the link to verify the request immediately','Reply with your details to see if it is real','Forward it to all your contacts as a precaution','Delete it or verify through official channels without clicking','D','Beginner','Phishing emails'),(11,'Which of the following helps protect your device while browsing?','Keeping your browser and security software updated','Using public Wi-Fi for banking','Turning off your antivirus software','Clicking every pop-up for downloads','A','Beginner','Safe Browsing'),(12,'Which of these is a red flag of an OTP scam?','You receive an OTP after you tried to log in','You get a message asking you to enter an OTP on the official app','A message or call demands you share an OTP immediately with no reason','An app sends an OTP for password change you initiated','C','Beginner','OTP scams'),(13,'What is a \"man-in-the-middle\" attack on public Wi-Fi?','A slow internet issue','When a hacker secretly watches or steals data as it travels between you and the website','When someone sits next to you while you browse','A software update','B','Beginner','Public WiFi Risks'),(14,'Why is it dangerous to share your OTP with someone who contacts you unexpectedly?','They may use it to access your accounts and steal money','They can send you more messages','They will call again later','You will get extra notifications','A','Beginner','OTP scams'),(15,'Why should you avoid using unsecured public Wi-Fi for sensitive activities like banking?','Because it is slower','Because the screen blinks','Because it charges fees','Because it can let hackers intercept your data','D','Beginner','Safe Browsing'),(16,'What should you be suspicious of when you hover over a link in an email?','A long URL with a domain name you do not recognize','A link that matches the company brand perfectly','A link that shows a secure https prefix','A simple text link with no URL','A','Beginner','Phishing emails'),(17,'If someone calls you out of the blue asking for your OTP to \"fix a problem\" with your bank account, what should you do?','Share the OTP right away','Press any buttons they tell you to on the call','Give them personal info too','Call the bank using the number on your card to check','D','Beginner','OTP scams'),(18,'Which of the following helps protect you when using public Wi-Fi?','Using a VPN to encrypt your internet traffic','Entering your passwords on every site','Staying connected to as many hotspots as possible','Leaving file sharing on','A','Beginner','Public WiFi Risks'),(19,'A phishing email might greet you with \"Dear Customer\" instead of your name. What red flag is this?','Personalized greeting','Generic or impersonal greeting','Official business tone','Informal chat style','B','Beginner','Phishing emails'),(20,'According to the FTC, what should you look for before entering personal info on a site while on public Wi-Fi?','Ads on the page','If there is an offer in bold letters','How many pics are on the site','Whether the URL starts with https and shows a padlock','D','Beginner','Public WiFi Risks'),(21,'Turning off your firewall makes your device:','Safer','Faster and more secure','More exposed to attacks','Immune to malware','C','Intermediate','Firewall'),(22,'Why are software updates important?','They change the app color','They fix security weaknesses and bugs','They delete your files','They slow down your device','B','Intermediate','Software Updates'),(23,'What can happen if you ignore updates?','Nothing ever happens','Your device becomes more secure','Hackers can exploit unpatched vulnerabilities','Your battery improves','C','Intermediate','Software Updates'),(24,'Automatic updates are recommended because they:','Make devices heavier','Install security fixes without you forgetting','Remove antivirus','Delete apps','B','Intermediate','Software Updates'),(25,'Which device should be updated regularly?','Only laptops','Only phones','Only apps','All devices and apps','D','Intermediate','Software Updates'),(26,'What is malware?','A hardware cable','A type of secure software','Malicious software designed to harm devices','A WiFi booster','C','Intermediate','Malware'),(27,'Which of these is an example of malware?','Antivirus','Firewall','Ransomware','Software update','C','Intermediate','Malware'),(28,'How does malware commonly enter devices?','Through trusted updates','By clicking suspicious links or downloads','Through charging cables','By turning off WiFi','B','Intermediate','Malware'),(29,'What does ransomware do?','Speeds up your phone','Encrypts your files and demands money','Fixes security bugs','Blocks ads','B','Intermediate','Malware'),(30,'Which action helps prevent malware?','Downloading cracked software','Clicking pop-ups','Using antivirus and avoiding unknown links','Sharing passwords','C','Intermediate','Malware'),(31,'What is a firewall?','A physical wall','A security system that controls incoming and outgoing network traffic','A virus','A WiFi password','B','Intermediate','Firewall'),(32,'The main purpose of a firewall is to:','Increase internet speed','Block unauthorized access','Delete files','Improve graphics','B','Intermediate','Firewall'),(33,'A firewall protects against:','Physical theft','Unauthorized network access','Battery drain','Screen damage','B','Intermediate','Firewall'),(34,'Where can firewalls be found?','Only in big companies','Only in banks','In personal computers and routers too','Only in antivirus labs','C','Intermediate','Firewall'),(35,'Turning off your firewall makes your device:','Safer','Faster and more secure','More exposed to attacks','Immune to malware','C','Intermediate','Firewall'),(36,'Why should you lock your device?','To save battery','To prevent unauthorized access','To increase storage','To improve WiFi','B','Intermediate','Locking Devices'),(37,'Which is the strongest lock method?','1234 PIN','Swipe pattern like L shape','Strong password or biometric authentication','No lock','C','Intermediate','Locking Devices'),(38,'What can happen if your unlocked phone is stolen?','Nothing serious','Thief can access personal data','It automatically deletes everything','It locks itself later','B','Intermediate','Locking Devices'),(39,'Auto-lock feature helps by:','Shutting down your phone','Locking your device after inactivity','Deleting apps','Disabling camera','B','Intermediate','Locking Devices'),(40,'Why should laptops also have passwords?','Only phones need protection','Laptops store sensitive data too','Passwords slow them down','It is optional always','B','Intermediate','Locking Devices'),(41,'Why is RSA considered asymmetric?','A. It uses two different keys','B. It is faster than AES','C. It works only offline','D. It hides IP addresses','A','Hard','CRYPTOGRAPHY'),(42,'Which scenario shows a misconception about VPNs?','A. Using VPN on public WiFi','B. Thinking VPN makes you immune to phishing','C. Encrypting traffic','D. Hiding your IP from websites','B','Hard','VPN'),(43,'Advanced malware may evade sandbox detection by:','A. Encrypting WiFi','B. Detecting virtual environments and delaying execution','C. Using HTTPS','D. Updating antivirus','B','Hard','SANDBOXING'),(44,'Credential stuffing primarily relies on:','A. Guessing passwords manually','B. Stealing session cookies','C. Reusing leaked username and password combinations','D. Installing ransomware','C','Hard','CREDENTIAL STUFFING'),(45,'Which statement best describes how a VPN protects user traffic on public networks?','A. It blocks all malware automatically','B. It replaces antivirus software','C. It encrypts data between the user and the VPN server','D. It makes users anonymous everywhere','C','Hard','VPN'),(46,'What does a hash function primarily ensure?','A. Confidentiality','B. Data integrity','C. Network speed','D. IP masking','B','Hard','CRYPTOGRAPHY'),(47,'What is the primary purpose of sandboxing in cybersecurity?','A. Speed up programs','B. Isolate suspicious code in a controlled environment','C. Increase RAM','D. Encrypt passwords','B','Hard','SANDBOXING'),(48,'Which defense most directly reduces credential stuffing risk?','A. Disabling HTTPS','B. Multi-Factor Authentication','C. Slower internet','D. Public WiFi','B','Hard','CREDENTIAL STUFFING'),(49,'In asymmetric cryptography, which key is shared publicly?','A. Private key','B. Secret key','C. Public key','D. Session key','C','Hard','CRYPTOGRAPHY'),(50,'Why can a VPN provider still see your traffic even though it is encrypted?','A. Encryption does not work','B. The VPN decrypts traffic before forwarding it','C. VPNs cannot encrypt data','D. ISPs control VPN servers','B','Hard','VPN'),(51,'Which statement best explains sandbox limitations?','A. It prevents all cyberattacks','B. It cannot analyze encrypted files','C. Sophisticated malware can behave differently in sandbox environments','D. It replaces firewalls completely','C','Hard','SANDBOXING'),(52,'Credential stuffing differs from brute force because it:','A. Tries random passwords','B. Uses previously leaked credentials','C. Targets hardware','D. Requires physical access','B','Hard','CREDENTIAL STUFFING'),(53,'What happens if a private key is compromised?','A. Nothing serious','B. Encryption becomes stronger','C. Confidentiality and authenticity are broken','D. Hash values disappear','C','Hard','CRYPTOGRAPHY'),(54,'Which risk still exists when using a VPN?','A. No tracking is possible','B. Malware infections from downloaded files','C. Websites cannot log your activity','D. Your IP address never changes','B','Hard','VPN'),(55,'Sandboxing primarily protects against:','A. Hardware theft','B. Malicious code execution','C. Weak passwords','D. Slow browsers','B','Hard','SANDBOXING'),(56,'Why is credential stuffing highly effective?','A. People use strong unique passwords','B. Many users reuse passwords across sites','C. Websites never rate limit logins','D. It bypasses encryption','B','Hard','CREDENTIAL STUFFING'),(57,'What is the primary goal of symmetric encryption?','A. Digital signatures','B. Secure key exchange','C. Fast encryption using a shared secret key','D. Public key distribution','C','Hard','CRYPTOGRAPHY'),(58,'What is a \"no-log policy\" in VPN services?','A. The VPN blocks logins','B. The VPN promises not to store user activity data','C. The VPN deletes cookies','D. The VPN prevents hacking completely','B','Hard','VPN'),(59,'Why do security systems use sandboxing for email attachments?','A. To delete emails','B. To observe file behavior safely before delivery','C. To compress files','D. To hide metadata','B','Hard','SANDBOXING'),(60,'What tool do attackers commonly use in credential stuffing?','A. Antivirus','B. Automated bots','C. Firewalls','D. VPN routers','B','Hard','CREDENTIAL STUFFING');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `questions` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
