INSERT INTO `questions_new` VALUES (1,'What is an \"evil twin\" Wi-Fi network?','A network that doubles your connection speed','A personal hotspot from your phone','A fake Wi-Fi hotspot set up by an attacker to trick you into connecting','A private home Wi-Fi','C','Beginner','Level_1','Public WiFi Risks','An evil twin Wi-Fi network is a fake hotspot created by attackers to mimic a real network and steal user data.'),(2,'Which of the following is a common sign that an email might be phishing?','The email arrives from a domain you always use','The email uses your real full name in the greeting','The email has spelling errors and weird grammar','The email contains only plain text with no links','C','Beginner','Level_1','Phishing emails','Phishing emails often contain spelling mistakes and poor grammar because they are created quickly or by non-native speakers.'),(3,'Why can using public Wi-Fi be risky?','Because it always has a strong password','Because strangers on the same network might intercept your data','Because your phone would not be charge','Because it boosts internet speed','B','Beginner','Level_1','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi is risky because attackers on the same network can intercept sensitive data you transmit.'),(4,'What is an OTP scam?','A promo code for discounts','A trick where scammers get you to share your one-time password','A bank service update','A phone network upgrade','B','Beginner','Level_1','OTP scams','An OTP scam tricks users into sharing their one-time password so scammers can access accounts.'),(5,'What should you check before entering personal info on a website?','If the website loads fast','If the URL starts with https and has a padlock icon','If the background color is pretty','If the site has lots of ads','B','Beginner','Level_1','Safe Browsing','HTTPS and the padlock icon indicate the connection is encrypted and safer for entering personal data.'),(6,'Which statement about OTPs is TRUE?','OTPs can be safely shared with customer care executives','OTPs should be posted in group chats for verification','OTPs are private codes and should never be shared with anyone','OTPs remain valid for several days','C','Beginner','Level_1','OTP scams','OTPs are confidential security codes meant only for the account holder and must never be shared.'),(7,'A safe browsing habit is to:','Use the same weak password everywhere','Download files from unknown pop-ups','Only click links from trusted sources','Allow every site to access your camera','C','Beginner','Level_1','Safe Browsing','Clicking links only from trusted sources reduces the risk of malware and phishing attacks.'),(8,'If an email claims you must \"act now to avoid losing access to your account,\" what red flag is this showing?','Legitimate company urgency','Sense of urgency designed to rush you','Proper business communication','A friendly reminder','B','Beginner','Level_1','Phishing emails','Phishing emails create urgency to pressure victims into acting without thinking.'),(9,'What is a warning sign that a website might be unsafe?','It asks you to solve a captcha','It automatically starts downloading strange files','It has normal spelling and design','It asks you to sign in','B','Beginner','Level_1','Safe Browsing','Automatic downloads of unknown files are a strong sign the website may be malicious.'),(10,'According to phishing guidance, what should you do if an unexpected email asks for passwords or credit card details?','Click the link to verify the request immediately','Reply with your details to see if it is real','Forward it to all your contacts as a precaution','Delete it or verify through official channels without clicking','D','Beginner','Level_1','Phishing emails','Unexpected requests for passwords or card details should be deleted or verified through official channels.'),(11,'Which of the following helps protect your device while browsing?','Keeping your browser and security software updated','Using public Wi-Fi for banking','Turning off your antivirus software','Clicking every pop-up for downloads','A','Beginner','Level_1','Safe Browsing','Updating browsers and security software fixes vulnerabilities and improves protection.'),(12,'Which of these is a red flag of an OTP scam?','You receive an OTP after you tried to log in','You get a message asking you to enter an OTP on the official app','A message or call demands you share an OTP immediately with no reason','An app sends an OTP for password change you initiated','C','Beginner','Level_1','OTP scams','Scammers often demand OTPs urgently without valid reason - a major red flag.'),(13,'What is a \"man-in-the-middle\" attack on public Wi-Fi?','A slow internet issue','When a hacker secretly watches or steals data as it travels between you and the website','When someone sits next to you while you browse','A software update','B','Beginner','Level_1','Public WiFi Risks','A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when hackers secretly intercept data between users and websites.'),(14,'Why is it dangerous to share your OTP with someone who contacts you unexpectedly?','They may use it to access your accounts and steal money','They can send you more messages','They will call again later','You will get extra notifications','A','Beginner','Level_1','OTP scams','Sharing OTPs allows attackers to access bank or online accounts and steal funds.'),(15,'Why should you avoid using unsecured public Wi-Fi for sensitive activities like banking?','Because it is slower','Because the screen blinks','Because it charges fees','Because it can let hackers intercept your data','D','Beginner','Level_1','Safe Browsing','Unsecured public Wi-Fi allows hackers to intercept sensitive activities like banking.'),(16,'What should you be suspicious of when you hover over a link in an email?','A long URL with a domain name you do not recognize','A link that matches the company brand perfectly','A link that shows a secure https prefix','A simple text link with no URL','A','Beginner','Level_1','Phishing emails','Suspicious or mismatched URLs often indicate phishing links.'),(17,'If someone calls you out of the blue asking for your OTP to \"fix a problem\" with your bank account, what should you do?','Share the OTP right away','Press any buttons they tell you to on the call','Give them personal info too','Call the bank using the number on your card to check','D','Beginner','Level_1','OTP scams','Banks never ask for OTPs on calls - always verify using official contact numbers.'),(18,'Which of the following helps protect you when using public Wi-Fi?','Using a VPN to encrypt your internet traffic','Entering your passwords on every site','Staying connected to as many hotspots as possible','Leaving file sharing on','A','Beginner','Level_1','Public WiFi Risks','A VPN encrypts your traffic, protecting data on public Wi-Fi.'),(19,'A phishing email might greet you with \"Dear Customer\" instead of your name. What red flag is this?','Personalized greeting','Generic or impersonal greeting','Official business tone','Informal chat style','B','Beginner','Level_1','Phishing emails','Generic greetings like \"Dear Customer\" indicate mass phishing emails.'),(20,'According to the FTC, what should you look for before entering personal info on a site while on public Wi-Fi?','Ads on the page','If there is an offer in bold letters','How many pics are on the site','Whether the URL starts with https and shows a padlock','D','Beginner','Level_1','Public WiFi Risks','HTTPS and padlock symbols confirm encrypted communication even on public Wi-Fi.'),(21,'Which email address detail is often faked in phishing emails?','The font size','The sender display name','The email background color','The email timestamp','B','Beginner','Level_2','Phishing emails','Phishers fake sender display names to appear legitimate.'),(22,'What is Public Wi-Fi?','Private home network','Open internet network available to everyone','Office LAN','Mobile data','B','Beginner','Level_2','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi is an open network accessible to anyone nearby.'),(23,'Which is a strong password practice?','Using your name','Using 123456','Using mix of letters, numbers, symbols','Using \"password\"','C','Beginner','Level_2','Safe Browsing','Strong passwords combine letters, numbers, and symbols to resist hacking.'),(24,'If someone asks for your OTP to \"cancel a transaction,\" what is it likely to be?','A bank policy','A scam attempt','A service survey','A refund process','B','Beginner','Level_2','OTP scams','Requests for OTPs to cancel transactions are common scam tactics.'),(25,'What does HTTPS stand for?','HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure','High Transfer Text Protocol','Hyper Tool Protocol Service','None','A','Beginner','Level_2','Safe Browsing','HTTPS stands for HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure - encrypted web communication.'),(26,'Public Wi-Fi is commonly found in:','Banks only','Cafes, airports, hotels','Homes only','Factories','B','Beginner','Level_2','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi is commonly available in cafes, airports, and hotels.'),(27,'What is a common goal of phishing emails?','To improve your device performance','To steal sensitive information','To update your software','To reduce spam','B','Beginner','Level_2','Phishing emails','Phishing emails aim to steal sensitive data like passwords and card details.'),(28,'What does OTP stand for?','One Time Password','Online Transaction Process','Open Transfer Protocol','One Type Permission','A','Beginner','Level_2','OTP scams','OTP means One Time Password - a temporary verification code.'),(29,'Which activity is safest on public Wi-Fi?','Banking','Shopping','Reading news','Logging into email','C','Beginner','Level_2','Public WiFi Risks','Reading news is safer since it usually does not involve sensitive logins.'),(30,'Which attachment type in an unexpected email should raise suspicion?','A file you requested from your manager','A random ZIP or executable file you were not expecting','A PDF from a trusted client','An image from a known contact','B','Beginner','Level_2','Phishing emails','Unexpected ZIP or executable files may contain malware.'),(31,'What does \"Safe Browsing\" mean?','Shopping online','Protecting personal data while using the internet','Playing games','Sending emails','B','Beginner','Level_2','Safe Browsing','Safe browsing means protecting personal and financial data online.'),(32,'Main risk of public Wi-Fi is:','Slow speed','Data theft','Free access','Limited range','B','Beginner','Level_2','Public WiFi Risks','The biggest public Wi-Fi risk is data theft.'),(33,'If an email offers a prize you never signed up for, what should you do?','Click the link to claim it','Share it with friends','Ignore or delete the email','Reply asking for details','C','Beginner','Level_2','Phishing emails','Unsolicited prize emails are common phishing scams and should be deleted.'),(34,'When do you usually receive an OTP legitimately?','When you initiate a login or transaction','When strangers call you','When you win a lottery','When ads pop up','A','Beginner','Level_2','OTP scams','Legitimate OTPs are sent only when you initiate logins or transactions.'),(35,'Which symbol indicates a secure website?','Open lock','Warning sign','Padlock icon','Cross mark','C','Beginner','Level_2','Safe Browsing','A padlock icon indicates a secure encrypted website connection.'),(36,'Hackers on public Wi-Fi can:','See encrypted data only','Intercept your data','Increase speed','Block ads','B','Beginner','Level_2','Public WiFi Risks','Hackers can intercept unencrypted data on public Wi-Fi.'),(37,'Which language style is commonly used in phishing emails?','Highly personalized and accurate','Professional and detailed','Threatening or alarming language','Friendly casual updates only','C','Beginner','Level_2','Phishing emails','Phishing emails often use threatening language to scare victims.'),(38,'Where should you enter an OTP safely?','On official apps or websites you opened','On links sent by strangers','On social media chats','On unknown pop-ups','A','Beginner','Level_2','OTP scams','OTPs should only be entered on official apps or websites you opened yourself.'),(39,'Before entering passwords, you should check:','Website color','URL spelling','Ads on page','Font size','B','Beginner','Level_2','Safe Browsing','Checking URL spelling helps detect fake websites.'),(40,'What is a warning sign of an OTP scam call?','Caller asks you to keep the OTP secret from others but share it with them','Caller verifies your complaint ticket','Caller asks you to visit the bank','Caller schedules an appointment','A','Beginner','Level_2','OTP scams','Scam callers manipulate victims by asking them to share OTPs secretly.'),(41,'What should you do before downloading an attachment from an email?','Open it immediately','Verify the sender and scan for malware','Forward it to others','Disable antivirus','B','Beginner','Level_3','Phishing emails','Always verify senders and scan attachments to avoid malware.'),(42,'Public Wi-Fi is:','Always safe','Risky for sensitive data','Faster than private','Government owned','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi is unsafe for sensitive activities.'),(43,'Which of these emails is most likely phishing?','An expected invoice from your vendor','A password reset you requested','A security alert you did not initiate','A meeting invite from your team','C','Beginner','Level_3','Phishing emails','Unrequested security alerts are common phishing attempts.'),(44,'What should you avoid on public computers?','Watching videos','Logging into bank accounts','Reading news','Searching Google','B','Beginner','Level_3','Safe Browsing','Public computers may store credentials, making banking unsafe.'),(45,'Why do phishing emails often use logos of real companies?','To make emails colorful','To look trustworthy and legitimate','To reduce email size','To avoid spam filters only','B','Beginner','Level_3','Phishing emails','Phishers use real logos to appear trustworthy.'),(46,'A pop-up asking you to download software should be:','Trusted','Ignored unless verified','Always opened','Shared','B','Beginner','Level_3','Safe Browsing','Unverified pop-ups may install malware and should be ignored.'),(47,'What is a safe action if you suspect an email is phishing?','Click links to investigate','Reply asking if it is real','Report it to IT or the provider','Download attachments to check','C','Beginner','Level_3','Phishing emails','Reporting phishing helps prevent wider attacks.'),(48,'Which browser feature blocks unsafe sites?','Bookmarks','Safe Browsing filter','History','Tabs','B','Beginner','Level_3','Safe Browsing','Safe Browsing filters warn or block malicious sites.'),(49,'Phishing emails often try to create fear about:','Weather updates','Account suspension or legal action','New movies','Sports news','B','Beginner','Level_3','Phishing emails','Phishing emails often threaten account suspension or legal action.'),(50,'What is malware?','Hardware tool','Harmful software','Internet cable','Browser','B','Beginner','Level_3','Safe Browsing','Malware is harmful software designed to damage or steal data.'),(51,'Why do scammers ask for OTPs?','To activate your rewards','To gain unauthorized account access','To improve network speed','To update your SIM','B','Beginner','Level_3','OTP scams','Scammers ask for OTPs to gain unauthorized access to your bank or online accounts.'),(52,'Avoid entering passwords on:','Secure Wi-Fi','Public Wi-Fi','Home network','Office VPN','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi networks are less secure and can expose passwords to attackers.'),(53,'If you receive an OTP without requesting it, what should you do?','Share it with customer care callers','Ignore it and secure your account','Post it online','Forward it to friends','B','Beginner','Level_3','OTP scams','Receiving an unsolicited OTP may indicate someone is trying to access your account, so secure it immediately.'),(54,'What is \"Man-in-the-Middle\" attack?','Network speed issue','Hacker intercepting communication','Router failure','Software bug','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','A Man-in-the-Middle attack happens when a hacker secretly intercepts communication between you and a website.'),(55,'Which message is most suspicious?','OTP for login you requested','OTP for password reset you initiated','OTP asking you to share it to receive money','OTP from your banking app','C','Beginner','Level_3','OTP scams','Any OTP request asking you to share it for money or rewards is a scam.'),(56,'Fake Wi-Fi networks are called:','Mirror networks','Evil Twin networks','Ghost servers','Shadow routers','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','Evil Twin networks are fake Wi-Fi hotspots created to steal user data.'),(57,'Scammers may pretend to be from which organization to ask for OTPs?','Banks or payment services','Weather departments','Streaming platforms only','Gaming forums only','A','Beginner','Level_3','OTP scams','Scammers often impersonate banks or payment services to trick victims into sharing OTPs.'),(58,'A VPN does what on public Wi-Fi?','Slows internet','Encrypts connection','Deletes files','Blocks Wi-Fi','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','A VPN encrypts your internet connection, protecting your data on public Wi-Fi.'),(59,'What should you do if you shared an OTP by mistake?','Do nothing','Immediately contact the bank and change credentials','Turn off your phone','Delete messages only','B','Beginner','Level_3','OTP scams','If you share an OTP accidentally, immediately contact your bank and change your passwords.'),(60,'Which is safer?','Open Wi-Fi (no password)','Password-protected Wi-Fi','Unknown hotspot','Fake network','B','Beginner','Level_3','Public WiFi Risks','Password-protected Wi-Fi is generally safer than open or unknown networks.'),(61,'Which emotion do phishing emails commonly exploit?','Excitement only','Curiosity only','Urgency and fear','Boredom','C','Beginner','Level_4','Phishing emails','Phishing emails exploit urgency and fear to pressure victims into quick actions.'),(62,'How long is an OTP usually valid?','Several days','A limited short time','One year','Unlimited time','B','Beginner','Level_4','OTP scams','OTPs are valid only for a short time to enhance security.'),(63,'Which file type is most risky to download?','.exe','.jpg','.txt','.png','A','Beginner','Level_4','Safe Browsing','Executable (.exe) files can install malicious software and are risky to download.'),(64,'Hackers create free Wi-Fi to:','Help users','Steal data','Increase signal','Provide service','B','Beginner','Level_4','Public WiFi Risks','Hackers may create free Wi-Fi networks to steal personal and financial data.'),(65,'What should you check in the sender email domain?','If it matches the real organization','If it is colorful','If it is long','If it has numbers only','A','Beginner','Level_4','Phishing emails','Always verify that the sender domain exactly matches the legitimate organization.'),(66,'Which platform is safe for OTP sharing?','Email newsletters','Messaging groups','No platform is safe','Public forums','C','Beginner','Level_4','OTP scams','No platform is safe for sharing OTPs - they must remain private.'),(67,'Fake websites are created to:','Entertain users','Steal information','Provide news','Sell books','B','Beginner','Level_4','Safe Browsing','Fake websites are designed to steal login credentials and sensitive information.'),(68,'Automatic Wi-Fi connection should be:','Enabled always','Disabled','Ignored','Shared','B','Beginner','Level_4','Public WiFi Risks','Automatic Wi-Fi connections should be disabled to avoid connecting to malicious networks.'),(69,'Why do attackers send mass phishing emails?','To test internet speed','To reach many potential victims','To update contacts','To reduce spam','B','Beginner','Level_4','Phishing emails','Mass phishing emails increase the chances of finding victims who may fall for the scam.'),(70,'Why do OTP scam messages create urgency?','To help you faster','To prevent you from thinking carefully','To reduce server load','To save time for banks','B','Beginner','Level_4','OTP scams','Scam messages create urgency to prevent victims from thinking carefully.'),(71,'Which is safest way to download software?','Ads','Unknown links','Official website','Pop-ups','C','Beginner','Level_4','Safe Browsing','Downloading software only from official websites reduces malware risk.'),(72,'Which data is most at risk on public Wi-Fi?','Public posts','Banking details','Weather updates','News articles','B','Beginner','Level_4','Public WiFi Risks','Banking and financial details are highly vulnerable on public Wi-Fi.'),(73,'Which action makes phishing more effective?','User awareness','Security training','Careless clicking','Strong passwords','C','Beginner','Level_4','Phishing emails','Careless clicking on suspicious links makes phishing attacks successful.'),(74,'Which device receives OTPs most commonly?','Microwave','Mobile phone','Printer','Television','B','Beginner','Level_4','OTP scams','OTPs are most commonly sent to registered mobile phones for verification.'),(75,'If a site looks suspicious, you should:','Continue browsing','Enter details','Exit immediately','Share it','C','Beginner','Level_4','Safe Browsing','If a website looks suspicious, exit immediately to avoid potential threats.'),(76,'Secure websites on public Wi-Fi use:','HTTP','HTTPS','FTP','SMTP','B','Beginner','Level_4','Public WiFi Risks','HTTPS encrypts data, making browsing safer on public networks.'),(77,'If you accidentally click a phishing link, what should you do first?','Ignore it','Enter details quickly','Disconnect and run a security scan','Share the link','C','Beginner','Level_4','Phishing emails','Disconnecting and running a security scan helps minimize damage after clicking a phishing link.'),(78,'If a caller asks you to read an OTP aloud, what should you do?','Read it clearly','Disconnect the call','Repeat twice','Record it','B','Beginner','Level_4','OTP scams','Never read OTPs aloud to callers - legitimate services do not ask for them.'),(79,'Browser updates help in:','Speed only','Security patches','Changing color','Ads','B','Beginner','Level_4','Safe Browsing','Browser updates include security patches that fix vulnerabilities.'),(80,'File sharing on public Wi-Fi should be:','Enabled','Disabled','Automatic','Public','B','Beginner','Level_4','Public WiFi Risks','File sharing should be disabled on public Wi-Fi to prevent unauthorized access.'),(81,'What is a common phishing tactic involving invoices?','Sending free receipts','Sending fake billing attachments','Offering discounts','Providing tax help','B','Beginner','Level_5','Phishing emails','Fake invoice attachments are common phishing tactics used to spread malware.'),(82,'Which URL is most suspicious?','https://yourbank.com','https://secure.yourbank.com','http://yourbank.verify-login.co','https://mail.yourbank.com','C','Beginner','Level_5','Phishing emails','Suspicious domains that imitate real brands are often phishing websites.'),(83,'What should you do after using public Wi-Fi?','Stay logged in','Log out of accounts','Share passwords','Save credentials','B','Beginner','Level_5','Public WiFi Risks','Logging out after using public Wi-Fi prevents unauthorized account access.'),(84,'Best protection on public Wi-Fi:','No antivirus','VPN + HTTPS sites','Sharing files','Saving passwords','B','Beginner','Level_5','Public WiFi Risks','Using a VPN along with HTTPS websites offers strong protection on public Wi-Fi.'),(85,'What is \"email spoofing\"?','Blocking spam emails','Sending emails with fake sender addresses','Encrypting emails','Deleting old emails','B','Beginner','Level_5','Phishing emails','Email spoofing involves sending emails with forged sender addresses.'),(86,'If an email asks you to disable security software, it is likely:','A system update','A phishing attempt','A training email','A newsletter','B','Beginner','Level_5','Phishing emails','Legitimate organizations never ask you to disable security software - this is a phishing sign.'),(87,'What type of scam involves tricking you to install apps and share OTPs?','Tech support scam','Lottery scam','Survey scam','Delivery scam','A','Beginner','Level_5','OTP scams','Tech support scams trick users into installing apps and sharing OTPs.'),(88,'Receiving repeated OTPs without action may indicate:','Account compromise attempt','Network strength','Battery issues','Software update','A','Beginner','Level_5','OTP scams','Repeated OTPs without action may indicate someone is attempting to access your account.'),(89,'Which device setting improves safety?','Bluetooth on','Firewall enabled','Hotspot on','AirDrop on','B','Beginner','Level_5','Public WiFi Risks','Enabling a firewall helps protect your device from network-based attacks.'),(90,'Why should you avoid clicking shortened links in emails?','They load slowly','They always expire','They can hide malicious destinations','They reduce email quality','C','Beginner','Level_5','Phishing emails','Shortened links can hide malicious destinations and should be treated cautiously.'),(91,'Scammers may send fake payment screenshots to:','Help you track payments','Convince you to share OTPs','Improve banking apps','Provide receipts','B','Beginner','Level_5','OTP scams','Fake payment screenshots are used to convince victims to share OTPs.'),(92,'What is a secure payment sign?','HTTP','HTTPS + padlock','Red text','Pop-up','B','Beginner','Level_5','Safe Browsing','HTTPS and a padlock icon indicate encrypted and secure payment connections.'),(93,'Two-factor authentication adds:','Extra security','Extra ads','Extra speed','Extra storage','A','Beginner','Level_5','Safe Browsing','Two-factor authentication adds an extra layer of security beyond passwords.'),(94,'Software updates help by:','Adding ads','Fixing security flaws','Slowing device','Changing UI','B','Beginner','Level_5','Public WiFi Risks','Software updates fix security vulnerabilities that attackers could exploit.'),(95,'Best way to stay safe from OTP scams is to:','Share OTP quickly','Ignore security alerts','Never share OTPs with anyone','Save OTPs in notes','C','Beginner','Level_5','OTP scams','The best defense against OTP scams is to never share your OTP with anyone.'),(96,'Clicking unknown links can lead to:','Discounts','Malware infection','Faster internet','Free games','B','Beginner','Level_5','Safe Browsing','Clicking unknown links can install malware or redirect to phishing sites.'),(97,'Which statement about OTP security is correct?','Banks ask for OTPs on calls','OTPs should remain confidential','OTPs can be reused','OTPs never expire','B','Beginner','Level_5','OTP scams','OTPs are confidential and should never be shared with anyone.'),(98,'Public Wi-Fi is safest when used for:','Financial transactions','Confidential work','Casual browsing','Password changes','C','Beginner','Level_5','Public WiFi Risks','Public Wi-Fi is safest for casual browsing that does not involve sensitive information.'),(99,'Which is safe browsing behavior?','Sharing passwords','Using pirated sites','Logging out after use','Clicking all ads','C','Beginner','Level_5','Safe Browsing','Logging out after use prevents others from accessing your accounts.'),(100,'Phishing sites usually:','Look fake and obvious','Look like real websites','Have no content','Are government sites','B','Beginner','Level_5','Safe Browsing','Phishing sites are designed to closely resemble real websites to trick users.'),(101,'What is a firewall?','A physical wall','A security system that controls incoming and outgoing network traffic','A virus','A WiFi password','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Firewall','A firewall is a security system that monitors and controls incoming and outgoing network traffic based on security rules.'),(102,'What does ransomware do?','Speeds up your phone','Encrypts your files and demands money','Fixes security bugs','Blocks ads','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Malware','Ransomware encrypts files and demands payment from victims to restore access.'),(103,'Why should laptops also have passwords?','Only phones need protection','Laptops store sensitive data too','Passwords slow them down','It is optional always','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Locking Devices','Laptops store personal and sensitive information, so passwords protect them from unauthorized access.'),(104,'Which of these is an example of malware?','Antivirus','Firewall','Ransomware','Software update','C','Intermediate','Level_1','Malware','Ransomware is malicious software that harms systems by locking or stealing data.'),(105,'The main purpose of a firewall is to:','Increase internet speed','Block unauthorized access','Delete files','Improve graphics','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Firewall','Firewalls block unauthorized users or malicious traffic from accessing networks or devices.'),(106,'Auto-lock feature helps by:','Shutting down your phone','Locking your device after inactivity','Deleting apps','Disabling camera','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Locking Devices','Auto-lock secures devices by locking them automatically after inactivity.'),(107,'Why are software updates important?','They change the app color','They fix security weaknesses and bugs','They delete your files','They slow down your device','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Software Updates','Updates fix bugs and security weaknesses that hackers could exploit.'),(108,'What can happen if your unlocked phone is stolen?','Nothing serious','Thief can access personal data','It automatically deletes everything','It locks itself later','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Locking Devices','If stolen unlocked, thieves can access personal data, apps, and financial accounts.'),(109,'A firewall protects against:','Physical theft','Unauthorized network access','Battery drain','Screen damage','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Firewall','Firewalls defend systems from unauthorized network access and cyberattacks.'),(110,'Which action helps prevent malware?','Downloading cracked software','Clicking pop-ups','Using antivirus and avoiding unknown links','Sharing passwords','C','Intermediate','Level_1','Malware','Using antivirus and avoiding suspicious downloads reduces malware risk.'),(111,'Turning off your firewall makes your device:','Safer','Faster and more secure','More exposed to attacks','Immune to malware','C','Intermediate','Level_1','Firewall','Disabling a firewall removes a major security barrier against attacks.'),(112,'Why should you lock your device?','To save battery','To prevent unauthorized access','To increase storage','To improve WiFi','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Locking Devices','Device locks prevent unauthorized people from accessing your data.'),(113,'What can happen if you ignore updates?','Nothing ever happens','Your device becomes more secure','Hackers can exploit unpatched vulnerabilities','Your battery improves','C','Intermediate','Level_1','Software Updates','Ignoring updates leaves vulnerabilities unpatched and exploitable.'),(114,'Which is the strongest lock method?','1234 PIN','Swipe pattern like L shape','Strong password or biometric authentication','No lock','C','Intermediate','Level_1','Locking Devices','Strong passwords and biometrics provide layered and harder-to-break security.'),(115,'How does malware commonly enter devices?','Through trusted updates','By clicking suspicious links or downloads','Through charging cables','By turning off WiFi','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Malware','Malware often spreads through malicious links, attachments, or downloads.'),(116,'Automatic updates are recommended because they:','Make devices heavier','Install security fixes without you forgetting','Remove antivirus','Delete apps','B','Intermediate','Level_1','Software Updates','Automatic updates ensure security patches install even if users forget.'),(117,'Where can firewalls be found?','Only in big companies','Only in banks','In pe