s legitimate software to trick users.'),(135,'Biometric authentication includes:','Passwords','Fingerprint & Face ID','OTP only','Security questions','B','Intermediate','Level_2','Locking Devices','Biometrics include fingerprint and facial recognition.'),(136,'Automatic updates help by:','Reducing storage','Installing fixes quickly','Disabling apps','Blocking internet','B','Intermediate','Level_2','Software Updates','Automatic updates install fixes quickly to reduce risk.'),(137,'Software firewalls run on:','Individual computers','Switches','Servers only','Routers only','A','Intermediate','Level_2','Firewall','Software firewalls run directly on individual computers.'),(138,'A worm differs from a virus because it:','Needs user action','Self-propagates across networks','Infects BIOS only','Cannot spread','B','Intermediate','Level_2','Malware','Worms self-propagate across networks without user action.'),(139,'Recommended auto-lock time for security:','30 minutes','15 minutes','1-2 minutes','Never','C','Intermediate','Level_2','Locking Devices','Short auto-lock times reduce unauthorized access risk.'),(140,'Delaying updates increases risk of:','Faster performance','Cyberattacks','Better UI','More storage','B','Intermediate','Level_2','Software Updates','Delaying updates increases exposure to cyberattacks.'),(141,'Which is an example of firmware?','Router OS','Word document','Browser tab','PDF file','A','Intermediate','Level_3','Software Updates','Firmware is low-level software controlling hardware devices.'),(142,'Keyloggers capture:','Screenshots only','Keystrokes typed by user','Wi-Fi signals','BIOS data','B','Intermediate','Level_3','Malware','Keyloggers secretly record typed keystrokes.'),(143,'Shoulder surfing refers to:','Remote hacking','Watching someone enter passcode','Malware attack','Phishing','B','Intermediate','Level_3','Locking Devices','Shoulder surfing involves watching someone enter credentials.'),(144,'Packet filtering firewall examines:','Entire file 