rmediate','Level_5','Malware','Updates plus antivirus provide strong defense.'),(193,'Hardware security modules store:','Photos','Encryption keys securely','Contacts','Messages','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Locking Devices','HSMs store encryption keys securely.'),(194,'Which OS update improves kernel security?','Theme update','System update','Wallpaper update','Font update','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Software Updates','System updates strengthen kernel security.'),(195,'Misconfigured firewall can:','Improve security','Create vulnerabilities','Increase RAM','Delete malware','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Firewall','Misconfigured firewalls create security gaps.'),(196,'Indicators of malware infection include:','Slow system + pop-ups','Faster performance','Better battery','Silent fans','A','Intermediate','Level_5','Malware','Slow systems and pop-ups indicate infection.'),(197,'Best practice for device locking:','Disable lock','Use strong password + biometrics','Share PIN','Write PIN on phone','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Locking Devices','Strong passwords and biometrics best protect devices.'),(198,'Update backups are important because:','Updates always fail','Prevent data loss if update fails','Increase speed','Remove malware','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Software Updates','Backups ensure that if a software update fails or corrupts data, the original data can be restored safely.'),(199,'Firewall is best paired with:','No security tools','Antivirus & IDS','Media player','Office tools','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Firewall','A firewall blocks unauthorized traffic, while antivirus and IDS detect and respond to threats, giving layered security.'),(200,'Best practice before updating critical systems:','Ignore update','Backup data & test updates','Disable firewall','Disconnect storage','B','Intermediate','Level_5','Software Updates','Backing up data and testing updates prevents downtime and data loss if an update causes system issues.'),(201,'What is a \"no-log policy\" in VPN services?','A. The VPN blocks logins','B. The VPN promises not to store user activity data','C. The VPN deletes cookies','D. The VPN prevents hacking completely','B','Hard','Level_1','VPN','A no log policy means the VPN provider does not store records of user browsing or activity data.'),(202,'Why is RSA considered asymmetric?','A. It uses two different keys','B. It is faster than AES','C. It works only offline','D. It hides IP addresses','A','Hard','Level_1','CRYPTOGRAPHY','RSA uses two keys, a public key and a private key, making it an asymmetric encryption method.'),(203,'Credential stuffing differs from brute force because it:','A. Tries random passwords','B. Uses previously leaked credentials','C. Targets hardware','D. Requires physical access','B','Hard','Level_1','CREDENTIAL STUFFING','Credential stuffing uses leaked username and password combinations instead of guessing randomly.'),(204,'What is the primary purpose of sandboxing in cybersecurity?','A. Speed up programs','B. Isolate suspicious code in a controlled environment','C. Increase RAM','D. Encrypt passwords','B','Hard','Level_1','SANDBOXING','Sandboxing runs suspicious programs in an isolated environment so they cannot harm the real system.'),(205,'Which risk still exists when using a VPN?','A. No tracking is possible','B. Malware infections from downloaded files','C. Websites cannot log your activity','D. Your IP address never changes','B','Hard','Level_1','VPN','A VPN encrypts traffic but cannot stop malware downloaded onto the device.'),(206,'What does a hash function primarily ensure?','A. Confidentiality','B. Data integrity','C. Network speed','D. IP masking','B','Hard','Level_1','CRYPTOGRAPHY','Security patches fix vulnerabilities that attackers could exploit in software.'),(207,'What tool do attackers commonly use in credential stuffing?','A. Antivirus','B. Automated bots','C. Firewalls','D. VPN routers','B','Hard','Level_1','CREDENTIAL STUFFING','Zero day vulnerabilities are unknown 