','A. Digital signatures','B. Secure key exchange','C. Fast encryption using a shared secret key','D. Public key distribution','C','Hard','Level_1','CRYPTOGRAPHY','DDoS attacks overwhelm servers with massive traffic causing service disruption.'),(215,'Which defense most directly reduces credential stuffing risk?','A. Disabling HTTPS','B. Multi-Factor Authentication','C. Slower internet','D. Public WiFi','B','Hard','Level_1','CREDENTIAL STUFFING','Malware is malicious software designed to harm or exploit systems.'),(216,'Which statement best explains sandbox limitations?','A. It prevents all cyberattacks','B. It cannot analyze encrypted files','C. Sophisticated malware can behave differently in sandbox environments','D. It replaces firewalls completely','C','Hard','Level_1','SANDBOXING','Ransomware locks files and demands payment to restore access.'),(217,'Which scenario shows a misconception about VPNs?','A. Using VPN on public WiFi','B. Thinking VPN makes you immune to phishing','C. Encrypting traffic','D. Hiding your IP from websites','B','Hard','Level_1','VPN','Spyware secretly monitors user activity and collects data.'),(218,'What happens if a private key is compromised?','A. Nothing serious','B. Encryption becomes stronger','C. Confidentiality and authenticity are broken','D. Hash values disappear','C','Hard','Level_1','CRYPTOGRAPHY','Adware displays unwanted advertisements and may track browsing habits.'),(219,'Credential stuffing primarily relies on:','A. Guessing passwords manually','B. Stealing session cookies','C. Reusing leaked username and password combinations','D. Installing ransomware','C','Hard','Level_1','CREDENTIAL STUFFING','Trojans disguise themselves as legitimate software to infect systems.'),(220,'Sandboxing primarily protects against:','A. Hardware theft','B. Malicious code execution','C. Weak passwords','D. Slow browsers','B','Hard','Level_1','SANDBOXING','Worms spread automatically across networks without user action.'),(221,'What is credential stuffing?','Creating fake accounts','Using stolen credentials to access accounts','Encrypting passwords','Phishing via SMS','B','Hard','Level_2','Credential Stuffing','Rootkits hide malicious processes deep within operating systems.'),(222,'What is the primary function of a VPN?','Increase hardware speed','Encrypt internet traffic through a tunnel','Store files online','Block antivirus','B','Hard','Level_2','VPN','Keyloggers record keystrokes to steal passwords and data.'),(223,'What is sandboxing in cybersecurity?','Encrypting files','Isolating programs in controlled environment','Blocking firewalls','Compressing malware','B','Hard','Level_2','Sandboxing','Social engineering manipulates people into revealing confidential information.'),(224,'Encryption converts:','Ciphertext \Z Plaintext','Plaintext \Z Ciphertext','Hash \Z Salt','Key \Z Password','B','Hard','Level_2','Cryptography','Brute force attacks try many password combinations until one works.'),(225,'Credential stuffing relies heavily on:','Social engineering calls','Previously breached username-password pairs','Malware installation','Hardware exploits','B','Hard','Level_2','Credential Stuffing','Salting adds random data to passwords before hashing for stronger protection.'),(226,'VPN tunneling refers to:','Physical cable routing','Encapsulation of data packets','Wi-Fi boosting','DNS caching','B','Hard','Level_2','VPN','Hashing converts passwords into irreversible coded values.'),(227,'Primary goal of sandboxing is to:','Increase CPU speed','Analyze suspicious code safely','Store backups','Monitor bandwidth','B','Hard','Level_2','Sandboxing','Digital signatures verify authenticity and integrity of digital messages.'),(228,'What is cryptography primarily used for?','Data compression','Securing information via encryption','Increasing bandwidth','Hardware authentication','B','Hard','Level_2','Cryptography','Certificates confirm the identity of websites and enable secure connections.'),(229,'Main difference from brute force attacks:','Uses random guesses','Uses real leaked credentials','Targets only admins','Uses phishing emails','B','Hard','Level_2','Credential Stuffing','HTTPS encrypts web communication to protect transmitted data.'),(230,'Which protocol is considered most secure currently?','PPTP','L2TP','OpenVPN','FTP','C','Hard','Level_2','VPN','Two factor authentication combines something you know and something you have.'),(231,'Sandboxes prevent malware from:','Executing encryption','Affecting host system','Using RAM','Accessing CPU','B','Hard','Level_2','Sandboxing','Access control limits system usage to authorized users only.'),(232,'Decryption requires:','Firewall rules','Encryption key','Hash function','Digital signature','B','Hard','Level_2','Cryptography','Least privilege gives users only the access necessary to perform tasks.'),(233,'Attack automation is done using:','Firewalls','Bots/scripts','VPN hardware','SIEM tools','B','Hard','Level_2','Credential Stuffing','Security audits evaluate systems for vulnerabilities and compliance.'),(234,'IPSec operates at which OSI layer?','Application','Transport','Network','Physical','C','Hard','Level_2','VPN','Penetration testing simulates attacks to identify security weaknesses.'),(235,'Which technology is commonly used for sandboxing?','Virtualization','DNS filtering','RAID storage','Load balancing','A','Hard','Level_2','Sandboxing','Incident response plans guide actions during cybersecurity breaches.'),(236,'Symmetric encryption uses:','Two keys','One shared key','No key','Hash only','B','Hard','Level_2','Cryptography','Data classification organizes data based on sensitivity levels.'),(237,'Why is credential stuffing effective?','Strong passwords','Password reuse across sites','MFA everywhere','Encrypted DNS','B','Hard','Level_2','Credential Stuffing','Backup redundancy ensures multiple copies of critical data exist.'),(238,'SSL/TLS VPNs operate at:','Application layer','Data link layer','Physical layer','Session