','Firewall blocks traffic','A','Hard','Level_3','VPN','Business continuity ensures services remain operational during crises.'),(249,'Which encryption is widely used in VPNs?','AES-256','DES only','MD5','SHA-1 only','A','Hard','Level_3','VPN','Risk assessment identifies and prioritizes security threats.'),(250,'Site-to-Site VPN connects:','User to website','Two networks','Two browsers','Router to laptop only','B','Hard','Level_3','VPN','Compliance ensures organizations follow cybersecurity laws and standards.'),(251,'Combo lists refer to:','Password dictionaries','Breached credential databases','Firewall logs','VPN keys','B','Hard','Level_3','Credential Stuffing','Combo lists are databases of breached usernames and passwords used in credential stuffing attacks.'),(252,'Which tool type performs stuffing attacks?','Password managers','Credential stuffing frameworks','Antivirus','IDS sensors','B','Hard','Level_3','Credential Stuffing','Credential stuffing frameworks automate login attempts using stolen credentials.'),(253,'Account takeover (ATO) is a result of:','DNS spoofing','Successful credential stuffing','Packet sniffing only','SQL patching','B','Hard','Level_3','Credential Stuffing','Account takeover occurs when attackers gain access using stolen login credentials.'),(254,'MFA mitigates credential stuffing by:','Blocking IPs','Adding second authentication factor','Encrypting routers','Changing DNS','B','Hard','Level_3','Credential Stuffing','MFA adds a second verification factor, stopping attackers even if passwords are stolen.'),(255,'CAPTCHA helps prevent:','Malware','Automated login attempts','Encryption failure','DNS leaks','B','Hard','Level_3','Credential Stuffing','CAPTCHA blocks automated bots from performing large scale login attempts.'),(256,'Static analysis differs because it:','Executes malware','Examines code without running','Encrypts payload','Uses VPN','B','Hard','Level_3','Sandboxing','Static analysis studies code without executing it, making it 