y features?','Encryption only','Authentication & integrity','Compression','Key storage','B','Hard','Level_4','Cryptography','Digital signatures verify sender authenticity and data integrity.'),(266,'What is sold on dark web marketplaces?','VPN servers','Stolen credentials','Antivirus tools','Firewalls','B','Hard','Level_4','Credential Stuffing','Dark web marketplaces often sell stolen usernames and passwords.'),(267,'What does VPN obfuscation help with?','Hide VPN usage from firewalls/ISPs','Increase bandwidth','Block malware','Encrypt storage','A','Hard','Level_4','VPN','VPN obfuscation hides VPN traffic so it appears as normal internet traffic.'),(268,'How do cloud sandboxes benefit security analysis?','Offline analysis only','Scalable remote malware analysis','Router encryption','Firmware patches','B','Hard','Level_4','Sandboxing','Cloud sandboxes allow scalable remote malware testing environments.'),(269,'What does PKI stand for?','Public Key Infrastructure','Private Key Internet','Protected Key Index','Public Kernel Interface','A','Hard','Level_4','Cryptography','PKI stands for Public Key Infrastructure which manages digital certificates and encryption keys.'),(270,'How does rate limiting protect against credential stuffing?','Encrypting passwords','Limiting login attempts','Blocking VPNs','Deleting accounts','B','Hard','Level_4','Credential Stuffing','Rate limiting restricts repeated login attempts to stop automated attacks.'),(271,'Which VPN protocol is considered outdated and insecure?','WireGuard','OpenVPN','PPTP','IPSec','C','Hard','Level_4','VPN','PPTP is outdated and insecure due to weak encryption vulnerabilities.'),(272,'What type of attacks target key exchange interception?','Storage devices','Man-in-the-Middle attacks','BIOS firmware','Firewalls','B','Hard','Level_4','Cryptography','Man in the Middle attacks intercept encryption key exchanges.'),(273,'What do sandbox logs typically capture?','Power usage','File, registry, network behavior','Screen brightness','CPU fan speed','B','Hard','Level_4','Sandboxing','Sandbox logs record file, registry, and network behavior of programs.'),(274,'What does Double VPN provide?','No encryption','Two layers of encryption/routing','Faster speed','DNS caching','B','Hard','Level_4','VPN','Double VPN routes traffic through two encrypted servers for extra privacy.'),(275,'How does password hashing protect credentials?','Storing plaintext','Converting passwords to irreversible values','Encrypting routers','Blocking bots','B','Hard','Level_4','Credential Stuffing','Password hashing converts passwords into irreversible stored values.'),(276,'What do Certificate Authorities (CA) issue?','Passwords','Digital certificates','Hash values','VPN tunnels','B','Hard','Level_4','Cryptography','Certificate Authorities issue digital certificates to verify identities online.'),(277,'How does container-based sandboxing work?','Hypervisors only','OS-level isolation','VPN tunnels','BIOS partitions','B','Hard','Level_4','Sandboxing','Container sandboxing isolates threats using operating system level virtualization.'),(278,'What does Perfect Forward Secrecy ensure?','Same key reuse','Session keys not compromised later','Faster hashing','DNS encryption','B','Hard','Level_4','Cryptography','Perfect Forward Secrecy ensures session keys remain secure even if long term keys leak.'),(279,'What do file reputation systems integrate with?','Sandboxing platforms','DNS routers','RAID arrays','BIOS tools','A','Hard','Level_4','Sandboxing','File reputation systems check files against known threat intelligence databases.'),(280,'How does salting passwords improve security?','DNS spoofing','Rainbow table attacks','Phishing','Keylogging','B','Hard','Level_4','Credential Stuffing','Salting adds random data to passwords preventing rainbow table attacks.'),(281,'Logging policy refers to:','Server uptime','Data retention of user activity','Firewall logs','OS logs','B','Hard','Level_5','VPN','Logging policy defines how long user activity data is stored.'),(282,'Which is considered broken/insecure?','AES','RSA-2048','MD5','SHA-256','C','Hard','Level_5','Cryptography','MD5 is considered broken due to collision vulnerabilities.'),(283,'Hypervisor-based sandboxes rely on:','Virtual machines','DNS filtering','Encryption keys','Password hashing','A','Hard','Level_5','Sandboxing','Hypervisor sandboxes rely on virtual machines for isolation.'),(284,'No-log VPN means:','No encryption','No user activity stored','No servers','No DNS','B','Hard','Level_5','VPN','No log VPN services do not store records of user activity.'),(285,'IP reputation systems block:','Secure users','Known malicious sources','Internal admins','MFA tokens','B','Hard','Level_5','Credential Stuffing','IP reputation systems block traffic from known malicious sources.'),(286,'Stream ciphers encrypt:','Block by block','Bit/byte continuously','Files only','Keys only','B','Hard','Level_5','Cryptography','Stream ciphers encrypt data continuously bit by bit or byte by byte.'),(287,'Which is a sandbox use case?','Email attachment analysis','Cooling systems','RAID backups','DNS caching','A','Hard','Level_5','Sandboxing','Sandboxing is commonly used to analyze suspicious email attachments.'),(288,'WireGuard is known for:','Slow speed','Modern lightweight protocol','No encryption','Hardware routing','B','Hard','Level_5','VPN','WireGuard is a modern lightweight VPN protocol known for speed and security.'),(289,'Credential stuffing success metric measures:','Packet loss','Login success rate','DNS resolution','CPU usage','B','Hard','Level_5','Credential Stuffing','Credential stuffing success is measured by login success rates.'),(290,'DES key length is:','56 bits','128 bits','256 bits','512 bits','A','Hard','Level_5','Cryptography','DES uses a 56 bit encryption key which is now considered weak.'),(291,'Memory forensics in sandbox examines:','Disk sectors','RAM activity','GPU load','Network cables','B','Hard','Level_5','Sandboxing','Memory forensics analyzes RAM activity for hidden malware behavior.'),(292,'VPN latency increases due to:','Direct routing','Encrypted rerouting distance','DNS cache','LAN switching','B','Hard','Level_5','VPN','VPN latency increases because encrypted traffic travels longer rerouted paths.'),(293,'SSO risk in credential stuffing:','Limits access','One breach \Z multiple services compromised','Disables MFA','Blocks bots','B','Hard','Level_5','Credential Stuffing','SSO increases risk because one compromised account grants access to multiple services.'),(294,'Salting hashes prevents:','Keylogging','Rainbow table attacks','MITM attacks','Packet sniffing','B','Hard','Level_5','Cryptography','Salting hashes protects against rainbow table cracking attacks.'),(295,'Sandbox escape means:','Malware deletes itself','Malware breaks isolation','Sandbox crash','File quarantine','B','Hard','Level_5','Sandboxing','Sandbox escape occurs when malware breaks out of the isolated environment.'),(296,'Best use case for corporate VPN:','Streaming','Secure remote work access','Gaming','Social media','B','Hard','Level_5','VPN','Corporate VPNs enable secure remote access to company resources.'),(297,'Behavioral biometrics detects:','Password leaks','Unusual login behavior','DNS changes','Firewall breaches','B','Hard','Level_5','Credential Stuffing','Behavioral biometrics detects unusual login or typing patterns.'),(298,'Elliptic Curve Cryptography advantage:','Larger keys only','Same security with smaller keys','No encryption','Slower processing','B','Hard','Level_5','Cryptography','Elliptic Curve Cryptography provides strong security with smaller keys.'),(299,'Best enterprise deployment model:','Standalone only','Integrated with EDR/XDR','BIOS-based','Offline USB','B','Hard','Level_5','Sandboxing','Enterprise sandboxes work best when integrated with EDR and XDR platforms.'),(300,'Best enterprise defense strategy:','Password reuse','MFA + anomaly detection + rate limiting','Disable encryption','Allow unlimited logins','B','Hard','Level_5','Credential Stuffing','Combining MFA, anomaly detection, and rate limiting provides strong defense against credential stuffing.');
